Welcome back to the Griddle, our top picks from the week's Bloomberg Sustainability stories. Many people associate "Clorox" with century-old brand of bleach. How times change.  Clorox Co. (CLX)  is now aiming for a $300 million health-care products and services business,  mostly through acquisitions . The company wants to build on the success of Burt's Bees, the sustainable skin-care line that helped develop a  natural products standard  for its industry. Clorox is one of a growing number of companies pursuing sustainability practices both in the products it sells and by integrating its  financial and sustainability reports  to give investors a longer-term view of the full costs and benefits of its operations. And now the news: Ancient Killer Bug Thrives in Shadow of London’s Canary Wharf Water Leadership up for Grabs as Deception Fells Gleick Apple Pressured to Elect Board by Majority Thailand Proving Best Bet After China of Global Emerging Market Investors Romney as Audit Chair Saw Marriott Tax Shelter Defy IRS Weight Watchers Lures Companies Seeking to Trim Costs Wealthy Enriched by Double-Dipping in Program for Disadvantaged ‘Industrial Terrorism’ of Undercover Livestock Videos Targeted  BP Wins Most Pentagon Fuel Awards in Year After Gulf Explosion India May Spend $1 Billion to Map Aquifers, Avert Water Crisis  Oil Profits Slide Fastest Since Lehman Collapse on Gas Zap! Sustainability Means 'Deep Strategy'  